Nubia has released a new smartphone aimed at mobile gamers with a Snapdragon 845 processor and up to 10GB of RAM, reported Engadget. The Nubia Red Magic Mars features a variety of other features that are meant to entice gamers, including a vapor-based cooling system and an RGB light system that reacts according to what happens in-game. The device also offers a 6-inch 2,160 x 1,080 LCD screen, as well as built-in stereo speakers. To deal with the heavy battery usage of mobile games, Nubia has included a 3,800mAh battery in its new smartphone. Users can also plug in a joystick to both sides of the phone, effectively turning the device into a handheld console. There will be three available models: